                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d567">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/898.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Chargé d’Affaires</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-03-08T17:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 8, 1911—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department’s March 7, 10 p.m. Minister for foreign affairs much gratified to have
                    President’s assurance, but states no misgivings were entertained. The
                    mobilization is to-day the preponderating topic in all circles, the general
                    opinion being that it has some ulterior purpose.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dearing.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
